Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, let me ask you this:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what OPI stands for?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.79,0:00:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find that out and a lot more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.13,0:00:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the following report,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.50,0:00:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which will be given by Brother Paul Gillies,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who serves as the overseer of OPI.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.81,0:00:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 12:10 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.35,0:00:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“The congregator sought to find
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.55,0:00:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“delightful words and to record
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.85,0:00:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,accurate words of truth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.62,0:00:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In harmony with this principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.62,0:00:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Office of Public Information, OPI,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.13,0:00:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at world headquarters has, over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,been assigned by the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to convey accurate information
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.03,0:00:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to the news media and academics.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But as Satan intensifies\Nhis slanderous attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.14,0:00:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on Jehovah’s people\Nand opposers feed authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.48,0:01:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with twisted\Nand distorted statements about us,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.68,0:01:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,OPI’s assignment now includes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.55,0:01:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,conveying accurate words of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.25,0:01:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.69,0:01:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this report, we’d like to explain to you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.36,0:01:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how and why this work is done
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.42,0:01:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and also relate a few experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.23,0:01:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are Scriptural precedents \Nfor contacting government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.93,0:01:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah positioned\Nhis servants before rulers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.70,0:01:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to protect his people\Nand to further his purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.84,0:01:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Examples include Joseph before Pharaoh,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.81,0:01:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah before King Artaxerxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.85,0:01:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Esther and Mordecai before King Ahasuerus,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and Paul before Felix.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.49,0:01:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we do not need\Nthe permission of governments
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet and to preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do recognize\Nthat having religious freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cooperation of officials
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.66,0:01:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is conducive to spreading\Nthe Kingdom message.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.67,0:02:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,While remaining politically neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.20,0:02:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we provide accurate information
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.34,0:02:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘kings and all those in high positions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.28,0:02:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we may go on leading\Na calm and quiet life,’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.15,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as 1 Timothy 2:2 states.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.82,0:02:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, brothers\Nfrom OPI met with officials
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.39,0:02:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to address specific issues\Nhindering our work
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.89,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in Azerbaijan, Belarus,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia, and Central Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In July, a meeting\Nwas held with the prime minister
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.33,0:02:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of one African country to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the reasons for our Christian neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports such as these
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.61,0:02:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that document incidents of injustice
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.21,0:02:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,are provided to officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Many express appreciation\Nfor this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.95,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At a recent meeting \Nheld in Congo (Kinshasa),
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,an embassy official\Ncommenting on the quality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of these reports stated,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“They remain objective and moderate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.59,0:03:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the seriousness of the facts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we don’t take the initiative
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide accurate information,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.73,0:03:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,government officials\Nmay receive misinformation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.44,0:03:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,from opposers trying\Nto influence them to act against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, while it takes time and effort
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to counteract lies and misinformation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we have often experienced the truthfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Proverbs 25:15 tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.59,0:03:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“By patience a commander is won over,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.32,0:03:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and a gentle tongue can break a bone.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.06,0:03:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s now share\Nwith you some experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.73,0:03:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that demonstrate the benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of contacting both government officials
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.57,0:03:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.77,0:03:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding Russia,\NOPI keeps various officials
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world informed\Nof the ongoing harassment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and unjust detentions of our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.12,0:03:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, many of these authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.59,0:03:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,have issued strongly worded statements
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:04:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,condemning the ban in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,some of which you can find \Non the jw.org “Newsroom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, OPI communicated\Nwith journalists about Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,one of whom wrote a very interesting article
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.63,0:04:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for the international edition of Newsweek.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.67,0:04:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This article appeared on the front cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.54,0:04:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one outlet alone has published
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.54,0:04:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about 30 articles about the oppression
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nnot just in Russia but other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Each year in Uzbekistan,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers experience police raids,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.99,0:04:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,detentions, fines,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.19,0:04:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and sadly,\Nin some occasions, severe beatings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.86,0:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just\Nfor carrying out their Christian ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, often the reason for that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is because we have been consistently
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,denied registration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.44,0:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This photograph shows\Nsome brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who are maintaining\Ntheir joy despite all of them
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,having been fined exorbitant amounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.35,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now interestingly, on May 14, 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the ambassador from Uzbekistan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to the United States\Nsaid this in Washington D.C.,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nwill be able to register much easier.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So seizing this opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a delegation of brothers was approved
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.41,0:05:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to travel to Uzbekistan last month
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.21,0:05:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and held preliminary discussions
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with government representatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If it be Jehovah’s will,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we certainly pray that these efforts will lead
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.49,0:05:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to national registration
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and some relief for our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.59,0:05:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who have endured persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where appropriate,\NOPI also helps branches
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to organize public events
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.33,0:05:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in areas where our work\Nis often misrepresented.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, in Kazakhstan,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.51,0:05:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where there have been some obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:06:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,local officials and communities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.28,0:06:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have recently demonstrated a willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.31,0:06:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn more about Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the branch hosted\Na series of open house events
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in Kingdom Halls in select locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A number of officials, media representatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and other professionals\Nattended these events.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A government ministry\Nwrote to the brothers stating,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“These events will provide\Nthe citizens of our country
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.64,0:06:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“an opportunity\Nto learn more about the activities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.71,0:06:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the history of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in Kazakhstan and worldwide.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.01,0:06:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In Sri Lanka,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.08,0:06:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the cardinal of the Catholic Church\Nwrote to the president
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.65,0:06:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and other representatives of the government
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,demanding that they cancel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.09,0:06:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the special convention\Nthat was scheduled for just last July.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did the cardinal not get his way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.73,0:07:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but favorable government ministers\Nactually invited the branch
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold a press conference\Nto publicize the convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.37,0:07:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After OPI prepared\Nthe Sri Lanka branch for the event,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.91,0:07:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,approximately 45 media representatives
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,attended the press conference held at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the journalists\Nwho attended this press conference
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,also attended the special convention
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and published positive news stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.99,0:07:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of the clergy\Nsuccessfully influencing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.93,0:07:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,government officials\Nto cancel the convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.47,0:07:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,these officials\Nactually assisted us in publicizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the tools that we use
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.84,0:07:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for conveying accurate information
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.94,0:07:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the media and government officials
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the “Newsroom” section of jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.52,0:07:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, seeing the need
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for our brotherhood\Nto have a source of reliable reports
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,about current events\Ninvolving Jehovah’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.36,0:08:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of articles are now written
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.46,0:08:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with you in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.03,0:08:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a few have expressed appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.67,0:08:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for the “Imprisoned for Their Faith” feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.61,0:08:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which is now updated monthly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows us to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,imprisoned brothers by name in our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.65,0:08:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as an example, these are the faces
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of our young brothers in Turkmenistan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been imprisoned\Nas conscientious objectors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,during 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus foretold:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will be hated by all the nations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,on account of my name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.57,0:08:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we recognize that no amount of effort
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to educate government officials
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to change that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Pharaoh, some of the world’s dictators
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.05,0:08:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‘harden their hearts’ against Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.18,0:08:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Jesus also foretold:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.65,0:08:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will be brought\Nbefore governors and kings
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.86,0:09:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“for my sake, for a witness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.59,0:09:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to them and the nations.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.93,0:09:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not just OPI that is giving\Na witness to the governments,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it is every brother and sister\Nthat officials come in contact with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.77,0:09:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve often heard\Na government official say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.44,0:09:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that they know either\Na schoolmate, a former workmate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or a relative\Nwho is one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.38,0:09:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, each and every brother
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.22,0:09:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in prison is giving a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, on July 15, 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.56,0:09:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,during a press interview,\Nthe prime minister of Armenia
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.30,0:09:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,commented on his contact\Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.33,0:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was a political prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“There were prisoners, Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.57,0:09:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“who were there for not serving in the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.71,0:09:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“These people were convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about their beliefs.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.71,0:10:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he added,\N“You don’t have to agree with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but you could feel it was their conviction.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.42,0:10:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So who knows if someone\Nwho observes your conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or who you talk to\Nin field service or on public transport
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.93,0:10:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,may be the very person
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who one day is in a government position
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and knows something\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.94,0:10:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what you did or said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.44,0:10:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, we couldn’t do the work at OPI
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without you brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.88,0:10:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,setting such a fine example.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who work\Nin the Office of Public Information
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,under the direction\Nof the Coordinators’ Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consider it a real privilege\Nto support all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.73,0:10:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by communicating\Nwith government officials
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and representatives\Nof the media and academia
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—by conveying our beliefs and practices
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.80,0:10:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with “accurate words of truth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.65,0:11:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you kindly, Brother Gillies,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.32,0:11:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for that thought-provoking update
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.22,0:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,on the important work being done
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Office of Public Information.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how quickly I learned\Nthe meaning of that acronym.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you remember\Nfrom a previous annual meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Herd especially likes acronyms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.51,0:11:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Gillies,\Nwe know Britain misses having you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.51,0:11:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re very happy to have you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with us here at headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But you will have to learn how\Nto correctly say, “schedule.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.03,0:11:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But we love you anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, let me ask you this:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it seem like
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters around the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are being pummeled\Nwith more and more natural disasters?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.15,0:12:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you’ll find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.15,0:12:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother John Ekrann,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who serves as a helper
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.45,0:12:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Coordinators’ Committee,\Nwill give us the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.02,0:12:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find it very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.02,0:12:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Ekrann, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.16,0:12:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Two thousand seventeen and 2018
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.93,0:12:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,were certainly record years for disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.57,0:12:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at a few of the headlines
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.03,0:12:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,from the news in 2017 and 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There were earthquakes in Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.24,0:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,plague in Madagascar, \Nfood shortages in Venezuela
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,—disasters are going to get worse—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,war in Congo,\Ndeadly Nipah virus in India,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a volcano erupts in Guatemala,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.42,0:12:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,violence in Cameroon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ebola in the DRC.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we are not surprised
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.76,0:13:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because we see\Nthe increased frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.60,0:13:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and intensity of disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as fulfillment of Bible prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at Luke chapter 21
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.24,0:13:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at verses 10 and 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.14,0:13:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he said to them:\N‘Nation will rise against nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and kingdom against kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘There will be great earthquakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.42,0:13:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and in one place after another
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,food shortages and pestilences.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We are actually witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.93,0:13:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and can see\Nthe fulfillment of Jesus’ words.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We are seeing ‘earthquakes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in one place after another’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.94,0:13:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—and truly great earthquakes\Nas Jesus described.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.08,0:13:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Volcanoes dump huge amounts\Nof ash and smoke into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tornadoes, hurricanes,\Nand typhoon winds
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.09,0:14:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,destroy buildings and property.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Rain and flooding\Nfrom these huge storms
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.59,0:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,cause rivers to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and damage large areas\Nof lands and property,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.47,0:14:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,causing mud and debris\Nto flow into buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,like this expandable Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.47,0:14:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wildfires engulf both forests
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and communities in flames and smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.14,0:14:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving only behind the charred remains
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of what was once called home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when there is a disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us are keenly interested to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How are our brothers\Nand sisters doing?’
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The “JW News” section of jw.org
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is regularly updated with news
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.37,0:14:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of how our brothers and sisters\Nare affected by a certain disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just here, we see some\Nof the headlines
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that are on “JW News” lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.58,0:14:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and we encourage you\Nto read this section regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.38,0:15:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay up-to-date.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.78,0:15:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to show you the size and scale
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of disasters lately, look at this map
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as we plot on it the disasters that have occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in just the last service year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.89,0:15:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you notice the number of brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.90,0:15:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that are affected?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\Nclose to half a million of our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,were directly affected by these disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in just the last couple of years?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.84,0:15:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s sad to say that 22\Nof our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,died in these disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and 84 were seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.45,0:15:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Tens of thousands of our brothers\Nhave had to find new homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And of these, 14,000 had to\Ncompletely flee their homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.60,0:15:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we want all of you to know
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.23,0:15:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been affected\Nby many of these disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,just in the last couple of years
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.07,0:15:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that we love and pray for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.74,0:16:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not lost or forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says at Isaiah 49:15:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.75,0:16:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“I would never forget you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, proof that Jehovah\Nhas not forgotten you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.92,0:16:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the love of your brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Acts chapter 2\Ndescribes in the first century
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.69,0:16:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how the brothers then\Ntook care of one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.13,0:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts chapter 2 describes\Nhow our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.43,0:16:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,were willing to sell\Nproperties and possessions
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.70,0:16:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to help one another out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.90,0:16:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Acts chapter 11,\Nthe brothers sent relief aid
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who were facing\Na very great famine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how has\Nour united brotherhood responded
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.28,0:16:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to these disasters today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.42,0:16:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there’s a fine phrase\Nin Philippians 1:27
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.92,0:16:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that can show, really,\Nhow our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of us—\Nare helping one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.53,0:16:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians 1:27, it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only behave in a manner worthy\Nof the good news about the Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.60,0:17:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that whether\NI come and see you or I am absent,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“I may hear about you and learn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.01,0:17:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you are standing firm in one spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.07,0:17:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“with one soul,\N(and here’s the phrase)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.54,0:17:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“striving side by side
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.65,0:17:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for the faith of the good news.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one very big way
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.32,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can ‘strive side by side’\Nin helping one another
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is by our donations\N to the worldwide work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.49,0:17:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This chart gives you an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.76,0:17:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the cost of disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they’ve jumped in 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we spent on an average
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between five and seven million dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.47,0:17:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on disaster relief in past service years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.27,0:17:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But look, though, what has happened in 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.04,0:17:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in 2018, it has climbed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.85,0:17:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to over 33 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.85,0:17:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what will happen in 2019?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s already off\Nto a big start in September.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:18:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body asked\Nthat I pass along to all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks and appreciation\Nfor your generous donations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like to assure you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.57,0:18:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that your donations\Nare being put to good use
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in helping in one disaster after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.81,0:18:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, another way\Nthat we as a brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.25,0:18:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,work side by side
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.28,0:18:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is volunteering to assist in a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.32,0:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have willingly volunteered\Nto reconstruct or repair Kingdom Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or our brothers’ and sisters’ homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Others carry and deliver food, water,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.70,0:18:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other items needed\Nafter a disaster
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to help our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.37,0:18:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,by using any transportation means possible:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,horses, boats, trucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Some volunteer\Nwith paint rollers and brushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.38,0:18:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Others show up with shovels\Nto clean up after a disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.72,0:18:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,prepare meals for the workers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,put supply packages together,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.36,0:19:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort, bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.63,0:19:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and deliver them\N—all with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.10,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at all these happy faces!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to thank all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.10,0:19:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that have worked so hard\Non disaster relief,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.10,0:19:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the last couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We also want to thank\Nthe departments at headquarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.58,0:19:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the Branch Committees,\Nthe branch departments,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.05,0:19:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the circuit overseers, LDCs,\Ndisaster relief committees,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.05,0:19:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of you elders worldwide
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.39,0:19:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that have really pitched in\Nand helped so much
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with disaster relief efforts\Nthe past couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.16,0:19:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.46,0:19:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how do\Nour brothers and sisters feel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.63,0:19:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,about your love and support?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as you watch this next video,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.67,0:19:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to read\Nto you a sentence or two
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from different letters\Nof appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.01,0:19:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that our brothers\Nhave sent in following a disaster:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah knows\Nwhen we’re in need, and he spoils us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“by giving us\Neven more than we ask for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.69,0:20:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your deep concern\Nas well as the spiritual, emotional,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“and material support you’ve provided\Nand that we’re still receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.27,0:20:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“is a real soothing ointment\Nthat can help us to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.17,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“When we see our belongings\Ncovered with mud brought outside
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and thrown as garbage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.31,0:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“we feel very heartbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.51,0:20:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the brothers and sisters saw them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“not as a lump of garbage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“but as a mass of our feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“The day the construction brothers\Narrived at my home, I burst into tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.16,0:20:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’d like to clarify that I didn’t cry\Nbecause I was going to get a new house
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.50,0:20:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“but because I saw\NJehovah’s hand in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.04,0:20:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“The transformation\Nwas not limited to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.11,0:21:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“This experience has changed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.04,0:21:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’ve not only seen\Nbut also felt Jehovah’s tender care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.18,0:21:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“They not only repaired our house;\Nthey also repaired our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.25,0:21:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“We were able to see Jehovah\Nin this beautiful work
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.79,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“of strengthening help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even though\Nwe lost our possessions, being busy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.46,0:21:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the construction and preaching work\Nhelped us to maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.56,0:21:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“our emotional and spiritual balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.93,0:21:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“We felt a lump\Nin our throats at being witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.07,0:21:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to the tender care\Nof our protective God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.49,0:21:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can expect that disasters\Nare going to intensify
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as we get closer\Nto the end of this system.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.83,0:21:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The study note on Mark 13:8
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.23,0:22:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,on the phrase\N“pangs of distress” says this:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.37,0:22:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It may suggest that like birth pains\Nthe foretold troubles and suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.14,0:22:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will increase in frequency,\Nintensity, and duration
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.48,0:22:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the time period\Nbefore a great tribulation.’
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.95,0:22:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be next\Nto need help from your brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.02,0:22:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Be prepared, but at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.33,0:22:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t put trust\Nin money or your belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.70,0:22:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All can be gone instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,While nothing\Nof our possessions will last forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of Jehovah\Nand the love of our brothers will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.71,0:22:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As we face increasing disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s continue side by side
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.65,0:22:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to help everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—each one of us—\Nto survive this old system.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.47,0:23:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate very much, Brother Ekrann,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.17,0:23:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that enlightening report that you gave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.81,0:23:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those were\Nsome necessary announcements
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.48,0:23:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you needed to know about,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.75,0:23:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but we have two more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.98,0:23:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,very exciting announcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thought it would be better\Nif you were seated for these.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.42,0:23:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s the first one:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.79,0:23:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body has approved
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.70,0:23:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a significant redesign
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.77,0:23:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of the jw.org® website
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.97,0:23:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to include the features
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting®
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.91,0:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY™.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.08,0:23:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, the JW Library® app
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.61,0:23:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,will be redesigned and will incorporate
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.62,0:23:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the content and features
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.09,0:23:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of Watchtower Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.72,0:24:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the overall appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.82,0:24:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of the new website and app will be unified
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.43,0:24:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and become more user-friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.27,0:24:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Planning and design work
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,have already begun
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.10,0:24:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on this very large project.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You should see certain improvements\Nwithin a few months.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.31,0:24:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this time,\Nless than six months does apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.91,0:24:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.63,0:24:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s one more very exciting announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.56,0:24:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—especially for our field missionaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.17,0:24:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,some of whom may be here in attendance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.10,0:24:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll be happy you were seated:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For nearly 75 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.28,0:24:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilead-trained missionaries
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.04,0:24:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,have been serving in the worldwide field,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.08,0:25:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,opening up new territories
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.68,0:25:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as strengthening the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.69,0:25:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority\Nof these missionaries continue to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.76,0:25:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in field assignments\Nand have gained valuable experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.29,0:25:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We are pleased to inform you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.33,0:25:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Governing Body has given approval
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.93,0:25:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for all field missionaries
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.30,0:25:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with an FMF enrollment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.27,0:25:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been serving
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.27,0:25:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for at least five years to attend
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.31,0:25:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the School of Kingdom Evangelizers—SKE.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.65,0:25:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This provision will reinforce
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.52,0:25:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirituality of these dear ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.99,0:25:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be mixed into the SKE classes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.26,0:25:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,along with new students
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.39,0:25:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow others to benefit from their experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.63,0:25:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Approved missionaries will attend SKE
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.17,0:25:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the location of the school of the country
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.27,0:25:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to which they are assigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.09,0:26:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re all very happy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.59,0:26:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for you hard-working field missionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.76,0:26:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, Brother Herd\Nhas a couple more acronyms
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.93,0:26:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of this announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.93,0:26:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—the FMF enrollment
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.70,0:26:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and SKE classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.14,0:26:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So Brother Herd,\NI hope you took note of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.71,0:26:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, for the next one hour\Nand twenty minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.88,0:26:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to get to enjoy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.15,0:26:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some very exciting, fast-moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.12,0:26:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightening talks
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.12,0:26:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,given by five different members\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.06,0:26:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice, I highlighted\Nthat word “enlightening.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.93,0:26:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Our leadoff speaker
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:26:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is Brother Kenneth Cook
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.93,0:27:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,who will present the talk,\N“We Should Be Teachers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.11,0:27:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.91,0:27:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,After a convention, we often say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.94,0:27:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that the teaching\Nwas better than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.18,0:27:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But even the best teachers\Nat this convention
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.95,0:27:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or your convention\Nor on today’s program
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.35,0:27:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are no match\Nfor the Great Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.22,0:27:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was an exceptional teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.09,0:27:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what it would have been like\Nto hear Jesus teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.40,0:27:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What made him so effective?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.13,0:27:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have to guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.14,0:27:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider a few of the methods\Nthat he used in the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.61,0:27:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, his introduction
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.11,0:27:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,aroused interest and introduced his subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.81,0:27:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew chapter 5, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.05,0:27:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 3, Jesus simply said:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.39,0:27:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are those conscious\Nof their spiritual need.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.82,0:28:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That simple statement\Nprovided the interest for his listeners.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.76,0:28:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They would want to know,\N‘How would this make me happy?’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.93,0:28:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He then added:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.94,0:28:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . since the Kingdom\Nof the heavens belongs to them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.47,0:28:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.47,0:28:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that he consistently used\Nto mark his teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.28,0:28:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus also used effective questions\Nto reason with his listeners.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.25,0:28:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He crafted simple\Nbut powerful illustrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.75,0:28:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And if birds and lilies were on hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.32,0:28:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps he was actually using visual aids
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.29,0:28:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,during that Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.43,0:28:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, his conclusion was simple;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.93,0:28:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it was brief and motivating.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.20,0:28:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder Jesus’ listeners\Nwere astounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.67,0:28:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Jesus expect us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.67,0:28:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be merely astounded\Nat his teaching, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.31,0:28:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.74,0:28:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He commissioned his disciples\Nto ‘go preaching and teaching.’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.58,0:28:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul later plainly told\Nthe Hebrew Christians:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.72,0:28:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“You should be teachers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was effective teaching\Nso necessary then and now?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.76,0:29:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because lives are involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.63,0:29:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents, Satan is waging war\Nfor the hearts of your children,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.50,0:29:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s never been more important\Nto inculcate the truth in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.00,0:29:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It means their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.01,0:29:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders, our fellow worshippers\Nare battered by this system,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.38,0:29:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s never been more important
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.48,0:29:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage\Nand strengthen them to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.95,0:29:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It means their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.29,0:29:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And publishers, that’s all of us here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.66,0:29:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the end is rapidly drawing near,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.09,0:29:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s never been more important\Nto teach Bible truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.89,0:29:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in a simple, \Nappealing, and motivating way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.70,0:29:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It means life to those who listen to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.70,0:29:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because teaching is so important,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.07,0:29:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has motivated skilled teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.84,0:29:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to pass on their methods to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.61,0:30:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, the Bible tells us\Nthat Paul imparted to Timothy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.58,0:30:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not only what to teach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.92,0:30:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but also his methods,\Nor how to teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.12,0:30:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those methods, it says,\Nwere valid everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.29,0:30:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in every congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.66,0:30:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so Timothy passed\Nthose methods on to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.80,0:30:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Jehovah’s organization
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.83,0:30:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has endeavored\Nto follow the same pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.77,0:30:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Teaching teachers has a long history
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.51,0:30:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.78,0:30:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at some modern examples
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.81,0:30:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of how Jehovah has trained us to be teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.35,0:30:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1922, The School of the Prophets
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.92,0:30:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,was used by some groups of Bible students
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.59,0:30:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop the art\Nof public teaching and speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.03,0:30:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,One suggestion in the booklet
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.03,0:30:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was to practice a figure-eight gesture,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.53,0:30:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, so that speakers would learn
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.00,0:30:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to move their arms and hands in curves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.11,0:31:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those schools were later discontinued.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.98,0:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen forty-two
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.98,0:31:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—even before the Theocratic Ministry School
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.18,0:31:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,was introduced to the congregations—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.45,0:31:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a series of articles in Consolation magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.45,0:31:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared until 1945 under the heading
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.52,0:31:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Presenting ‘This Gospel of the Kingdom.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.53,0:31:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The first article stated the series’ purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.83,0:31:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It said: “To give\Nhelpful instruction and practical hints
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.07,0:31:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“to such ones as would publish God’s kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.14,0:31:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“after the example of Christ himself . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.51,0:31:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Study and apply this instruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.11,0:31:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and note your improvement\Nas a Kingdom publisher.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.35,0:31:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen forty-three
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.35,0:31:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—the booklet Course in Theocratic Ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.55,0:31:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,featured 52 lessons,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.75,0:31:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,one for each week of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.99,0:31:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in conjunction with the newly formed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.26,0:31:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Theocratic Ministry School.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.69,0:31:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen forty-five
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.83,0:31:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—the book \NTheocratic Aid to Kingdom Publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.30,0:32:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,expanded that course to 90 lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.14,0:32:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen fifty-five
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.50,0:32:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—the book Qualified to Be Ministers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.11,0:32:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was described in The Watchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.34,0:32:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as the “best yet” book
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.68,0:32:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Theocratic Ministry School
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.91,0:32:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,until it was revised\Ninto an even better qualified book
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.65,0:32:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1967.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.12,0:32:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineteen seventy-one
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.12,0:32:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Theocratic Ministry School Guidebook\Nwas released.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.53,0:32:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in 2002, we received
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.50,0:32:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Benefit From Theocratic\NMinistry School Education,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.73,0:32:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which included\Nnew study points, exercises,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.34,0:32:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and a counsel form right in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.44,0:32:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, as needs change, Jehovah provides us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with new tools to improve our teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.32,0:32:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it time for a new tool\Nto improve our skills as teachers?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.35,0:32:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the following\Nregarding our Ministry School textbook:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:33:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,(1) Terminology:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.26,0:33:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The contents\Nand even the title of that book
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.96,0:33:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,refer to the Theocratic Ministry School,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.80,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that, as such, is no longer in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(2) Simplicity:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.41,0:33:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Many find it difficult\Nto quickly find key ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book’s 53 study points.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.31,0:33:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,An elder from Georgia, U.S.A., wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.98,0:33:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the short time available\Nto direct the congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.15,0:33:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“to specific locations in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.72,0:33:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“it makes it very difficult for the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.32,0:33:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to find where the chairman is.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.29,0:33:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(3) Translation:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.33,0:33:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn’t easy\Nto translate a book this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.70,0:33:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in over 200 languages\Naround the globe,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.94,0:33:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,congregations have\Nthe Meeting Workbook
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.17,0:33:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but lack the Ministry School book.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.38,0:33:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For all of these reasons and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.04,0:33:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we are pleased to announce a release
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.35,0:33:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that addresses those concerns
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.82,0:33:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and that will help more\Nof God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.95,0:33:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve their teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.95,0:34:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a 28-page brochure entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.22,0:34:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply Yourself to Reading and Teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.37,0:34:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The chairman will let you know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.38,0:34:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can access a copy\Nfor your personal use
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.18,0:34:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—no doubt in less than six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.62,0:34:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, the instructions\N for Our Christian Life and Ministry Meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.22,0:34:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon be revised\Nand made available to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.13,0:34:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this brochure will be used
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.43,0:34:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at our midweek meetings worldwide
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.73,0:34:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning January 7, 2019.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.54,0:34:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t discard\Nyour Ministry School book, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.61,0:34:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we won’t be using it\Nat our weekly meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.27,0:34:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it is still a very valuable reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.11,0:34:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to know more about some
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.45,0:35:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of this new brochure’s features?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.46,0:35:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with brevity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.82,0:35:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only 20 study points,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.06,0:35:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and each study point is only one page long.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.06,0:35:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean important points\Nhave been omitted?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.93,0:35:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.27,0:35:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In many cases, similar points\Nhave been combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.34,0:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\N“Study 5—Accurate Reading,”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.34,0:35:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,incorporates key ideas from three points
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.91,0:35:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Ministry School book.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.91,0:35:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They are accurate reading,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.88,0:35:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,words clearly spoken,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.88,0:35:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and correct pronunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.05,0:35:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, reading accurately\Nincludes pronouncing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.12,0:35:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,each word correctly and clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.59,0:35:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.59,0:35:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the brochure does not suggest\Nusing that figure-eight gesture,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.93,0:35:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don’t have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.93,0:35:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Another feature is clarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.93,0:35:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Each study features\Ntwo or three main points
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.17,0:35:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with simple, direct instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.20,0:36:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and some study points\Nalso include practical tips
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that relate to the main point.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.44,0:36:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, you will find
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.51,0:36:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that many of the study points
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.55,0:36:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,include a box entitled “In the Ministry.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.48,0:36:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.92,0:36:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because while most\Nof the points in the brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.35,0:36:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,apply both to the field ministry\Nand to teaching from the platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.29,0:36:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,suggestions that are specific\Nto the field ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.49,0:36:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,appear in this separate box.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.63,0:36:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is a feature\Nthat you will really find of interest:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.77,0:36:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“Record Your Progress.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.00,0:36:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the last pages\Nof the brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.61,0:36:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is for you to record the date\Nyou consider each study point.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.58,0:36:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,More about that in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.65,0:36:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are some features.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.65,0:36:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But how will the new brochure\Naddress the three needs
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.68,0:36:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we mentioned earlier,\Nnamely terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.75,0:36:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity, and translation?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.72,0:36:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with terminology.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.46,0:36:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The brochure uses updated expressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.46,0:36:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but it does not refer\Nto specific meetings or meeting parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.90,0:37:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it will not need\Nto be frequently revised.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.04,0:37:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, simplicity: Fewer study points
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.21,0:37:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and a simple easy-to-use layout
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.41,0:37:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will allow the chairman\Nto isolate main points quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.25,0:37:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and will help the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.25,0:37:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to follow along closely \Nwith the chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.92,0:37:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, and you elders\Nare going to love this,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.62,0:37:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,more is being done\Nto simplify the work
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.23,0:37:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the chairman\Nand the Life and Ministry Meeting overseer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.10,0:37:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning January 7, 2019,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.77,0:37:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the instructions in the Meeting Workbook\Nfor each student assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.41,0:37:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,will include in parentheses\Nthe specific study point
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.61,0:37:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that the student should work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.98,0:37:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example,\Nfor the week of January 7th,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.45,0:37:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,all brothers worldwide\Nwho are assigned the Bible reading
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.45,0:37:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,will consider\N“Study 5—Accurate Reading.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.20,0:38:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought you would like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.67,0:38:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Life and Ministry Meeting \Noverseers and chairmen
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.71,0:38:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,will no longer need to worry \Nabout assigning study points
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.41,0:38:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or keeping track \Nof what each student is working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.11,0:38:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see a chairman use
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.25,0:38:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the new brochure to assist a student?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.52,0:38:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.76,0:38:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . and Abednego over the administration \Nof the province of Babylon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.83,0:38:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but Daniel served in the king’s court.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.10,0:38:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Gomez.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.43,0:38:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an excellent reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.04,0:38:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You were accurate, fluent,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.17,0:38:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and we could tell that you prepared well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.37,0:38:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You were working \Non study point number 10, “Modulation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.44,0:38:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The summary tells us that we have \Ntwo goals when modulating our voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.32,0:38:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One goal is to stir emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.82,0:38:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You stirred our emotions \Nwhen you read Daniel 2:47:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.39,0:39:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Truly your God is a God of gods.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.62,0:39:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,By raising your pitch, you conveyed \NNebuchadnezzar’s intensity and surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.53,0:39:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.70,0:39:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A second goal is to convey ideas clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.04,0:39:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to do it is to increase our volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.07,0:39:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nwhat is the main point of verse 44?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.38,0:39:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it that Jehovah will set up a Kingdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.31,0:39:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of emphasizing the word “kings,”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.32,0:39:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you might increase your volume\Nwhen reading “God of heaven.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.15,0:39:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the days of those kings \Nthe God of heaven will set up a kingdom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.56,0:39:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s something you might try\Nwhen preparing to read a scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.03,0:39:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for the main point in each verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.20,0:39:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then try varying your pitch, pace,\Nor volume to make that idea stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.37,0:39:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Gomez. Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.57,0:39:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,For our next part, we’ll consider . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.55,0:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very good example
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.62,0:40:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of concise and helpful\None-minute comments
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.02,0:40:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and counsel by the chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.36,0:40:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But where does the chairman write
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.39,0:40:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the student\Ncompleted the assigned point?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.23,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t write anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the page\N“Record Your Progress” mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.10,0:40:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who will write the dates\Nthat the student considered each point?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.24,0:40:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The student, not the chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.04,0:40:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When should a student\Nrecord a date on this page?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.94,0:40:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that’s up to you, the student.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.35,0:40:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Many will likely record the date
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.38,0:40:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are assigned \Nto consider a specific point
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.78,0:40:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for a student assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.89,0:40:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Others, including elders,\Nwho may not handle
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.92,0:40:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,student assignments regularly,\Nmay want to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.82,0:40:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,each of these points on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.23,0:40:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Each brother and sister\Ncan decide when and how
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.06,0:40:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to use this page\Nto record their progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.53,0:40:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This “Record Your Progress” page\Nis for your personal use.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.00,0:40:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, so far, we’ve looked at the need
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.04,0:41:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for updated terminology\Nand greater simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.94,0:41:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider\Nthat third point: translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.11,0:41:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be thrilled to know\Nthat the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.45,0:41:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,has already approved for this brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.78,0:41:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to be translated\Ninto over 350 languages
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.39,0:41:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—more than twice\Nthe number of languages
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.89,0:41:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that produce the current textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.16,0:41:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the same brevity that allows us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.16,0:41:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand the translation also means
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.30,0:41:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are few real-life examples\Nin the brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.87,0:41:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that show how to apply the study points.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.74,0:41:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So wouldn’t it be helpful to see\Nhow to put the study points into action,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.51,0:41:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,both from the platform\Nand in the field ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.41,0:41:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.15,0:41:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, the Governing Body\Nhas approved the production of 20 videos
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.02,0:41:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—one for each study point—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.05,0:41:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to depict the application of these points.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.12,0:41:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch the video
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.76,0:41:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for “Study 1—Effective Introduction.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.67,0:42:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re at the Kingdom Hall\Nabout to give a public talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.74,0:42:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the audience listen\Nto what you have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.75,0:42:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Much depends on how\Nyou introduce your subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.02,0:42:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,An effective introduction arouses interest,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.39,0:42:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,identifies your subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.79,0:42:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and shows why the subject\Nis important to your listeners.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.23,0:42:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s give our brother\Nan opportunity to introduce his subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.40,0:42:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As the meeting chairman mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.94,0:42:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to talk about death
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.20,0:42:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it means to you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.37,0:42:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read a scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.44,0:42:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at Ecclesiastes 9:5.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.75,0:42:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.15,0:42:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the speaker identify his subject?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.25,0:42:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.25,0:42:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he arouse interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.26,0:42:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.26,0:43:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he show why the subject is important?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.46,0:43:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.46,0:43:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So how might he approach\Nthe subject differently?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.57,0:43:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.60,0:43:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout all of human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.97,0:43:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not one person has escaped death.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.91,0:43:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The lives of some people\Nare cut short suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.85,0:43:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by unexpected events or illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.58,0:43:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever lost a loved one in death?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.29,0:43:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you know how painful that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.79,0:43:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet how can something\Nthat causes so much pain
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.19,0:43:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,be a normal, natural part of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.53,0:43:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible is the key
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.63,0:43:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to understanding why we die,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.50,0:43:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,where we go when we die,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.64,0:43:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and how death will be reversed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.14,0:43:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider each of those points.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.84,0:43:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can apply this principle
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.98,0:43:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to any subject when giving a talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.21,0:43:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can you effectively introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.35,0:43:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a subject in the ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.12,0:44:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, of course,\Nthat in most cases
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.12,0:44:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re a complete stranger\Nto the householder.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.69,0:44:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Try not to startle the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.83,0:44:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Identify yourself early in the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.80,0:44:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To determine what\Na person might be interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.50,0:44:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,observe his activities or surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.64,0:44:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You might begin by asking a question
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.07,0:44:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or making a brief comment\Nabout those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.38,0:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider one example.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.65,0:44:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, my name is Jill.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.68,0:44:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m here to talk\Nabout God’s purpose for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.72,0:44:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says here—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.19,0:44:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I don’t have time to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.99,0:44:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the introduction effective?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.10,0:44:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The householder didn’t want\Nto continue the conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.83,0:44:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so apparently the introduction\Ndidn’t arouse interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.10,0:44:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How might the publisher\Nhave handled the situation better?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.21,0:44:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.88,0:45:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a beautiful garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.88,0:45:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It must take a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.22,0:45:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure does!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.89,0:45:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your work is certainly paying off.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.22,0:45:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.56,0:45:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, my name is Jill,\Nand this is Tammy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.43,0:45:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.06,0:45:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily, you work so hard\Nto care for the garden you planted.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.57,0:45:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that God cares the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.90,0:45:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,about this planet that he created?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.78,0:45:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the publisher took into account
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.04,0:45:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the interests of the householder,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.25,0:45:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,she increased the chances\Nof starting a conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.45,0:45:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and sharing the Kingdom message.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.12,0:45:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This can also be done in urban areas
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.22,0:45:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where people expect you\Nto get right to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.99,0:45:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In such settings, try to include\Na thought-provoking statement
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.89,0:45:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or question in your introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.90,0:45:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Effective introductions are the first step
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.77,0:45:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,toward productive conversations
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.14,0:45:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and presentations of the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.56,0:46:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus foretold\Nthat the ‘preaching of the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.56,0:46:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Kingdom\Nwill stop when the end comes.’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.80,0:46:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So our work is urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.10,0:46:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the work of teaching\Nhas only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.23,0:46:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 26:9 says of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.54,0:46:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that “when there are judgments\Nfrom you for the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.24,0:46:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the inhabitants of the land\Nlearn about righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.58,0:46:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will certainly prove\Nto be true in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.71,0:46:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The great crowd will soon be invited
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.78,0:46:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach vast numbers\Nof resurrected ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.85,0:46:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You may study with someone\Nwho lived 3,000 years ago or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.79,0:46:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how helpful it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.33,0:46:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to have learned\Nhow to explain unfamiliar terms
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.46,0:47:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in “Study 17—Understandable to Others.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.27,0:47:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your student may have lived\Nduring the Middle Ages
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.94,0:47:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when people were taught\Nto fear the clergy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.47,0:47:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than to love God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.64,0:47:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But you will have already\Nlearned from Study 19
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.94,0:47:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how to “Reach the Heart” of your student.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.35,0:47:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you’re asked to summarize
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.38,0:47:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all that Jehovah did\Nfor his people during the last days,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.48,0:47:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll need to keep things simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.62,0:47:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,something you learned\Nin “Study 14—Main Points Made to Stand Out.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.63,0:47:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even today, however, we must be teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.33,0:47:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So use this new brochure\Nto ‘continue applying yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.40,0:47:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to reading and teaching.’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.40,0:47:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing this, the Bible tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.54,0:47:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will save both yourself\Nand those who listen to you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.25,0:47:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Brother Cook,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.29,0:48:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and thank you also\Nfor joining us on the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.56,0:48:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To borrow words from Brother Sydlik:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.43,0:48:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Lord knew we needed your help.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.93,0:48:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m still working on that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.37,0:48:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have the following announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.54,0:48:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding our wonderful new brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.14,0:48:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—and I double checked;\NI got the right announcement this time:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.51,0:48:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Teaching brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.82,0:48:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in all available languages
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.42,0:48:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,will be released on jw.org,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.66,0:48:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY™,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.29,0:48:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and JW Library®
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.66,0:48:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,on Monday October 8, 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.33,0:48:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in addition to that,\Nif you will be making use
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.07,0:48:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of a hard copy of this publication,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.91,0:48:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,one copy of the printed edition
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.64,0:48:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will be available after the program
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.44,0:48:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at the various annual meeting locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.95,0:48:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,including the main lobby of your complex
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.78,0:49:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for those watching from their personal rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.46,0:49:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional printed copies
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.52,0:49:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,may be requested through the congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.79,0:49:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So Monday\N—in two days—
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.90,0:49:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you get this one electronically.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.47,0:49:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, moving to our next talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.33,0:49:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re privileged to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.30,0:49:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to Brother Anthony Morris,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.31,0:49:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s going to deliver the gripping talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.08,0:49:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“This Is It!”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.08,0:49:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that I rendered justice
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.42,0:49:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to announcing that title, Brother Morris.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.47,0:49:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll talk to you later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.28,0:49:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It ruined my introduction, but that’s all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.19,0:49:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think all of you would agree
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.26,0:49:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how much we enjoyed the museum video
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.29,0:49:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and hearing Brother Fred Franz
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.83,0:50:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—his voice—\Ntalking about after the assassination
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.10,0:50:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the archduke\Nthat the brothers said, ‘Aha!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.50,0:50:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‘There it is!\NThere it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.37,0:50:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What we’ve been waiting for.’
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.01,0:50:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s very stirring,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.41,0:50:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we would have critics saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.78,0:50:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Yeah, but you people had other expectations
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.12,0:50:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that were not realized,’\Nand etcetera, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.49,0:50:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s amazing that even the world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.96,0:50:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,recognized that this was unique—1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.46,0:50:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NIn fact, I’ve had this for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.07,0:50:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.44,0:50:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s The New World Magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.67,0:50:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was widely read at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.97,0:50:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I guess about 1931,\Nthey went out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.08,0:50:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But here, \N“End of All Kingdoms in 1914
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.08,0:50:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—‘Millennial Dawners’ 25 Year Prophecy,”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.12,0:50:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,widely read; other newspapers covered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.36,0:51:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They made comments here:
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.83,0:51:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“The terrific war outbreak in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.49,0:51:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“has fulfilled an extraordinary prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.43,0:51:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For a quarter of a century past,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.00,0:51:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“through preachers and through press,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.54,0:51:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“the ‘International Bible Students,’\Nbest known as ‘Millennial Dawners,’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.34,0:51:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“have been proclaiming\Nto the world that the Day of Wrath
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.78,0:51:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“prophesied in the Bible would dawn in 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.18,0:51:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Look out for 1914!’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.58,0:51:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has been the cry\Nof the hundreds of traveling evangelists.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.12,0:51:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I appreciate very much how
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.22,0:51:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Yearbook in 1975
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.72,0:51:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,considering our modern-day history
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.36,0:51:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,made this beautiful quote:
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.16,0:51:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Disappointments about going to heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.00,0:51:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“in 1914 really were very minor,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.40,0:51:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“compared with the great expectations realized
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.71,0:51:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in connection with that year.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.71,0:51:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.01,0:51:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,During the first six months\Nof 1914, nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.78,0:51:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They were being ridiculed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.78,0:52:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the archduke is assassinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.49,0:52:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This one was particularly released
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.15,0:52:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on August 30, 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.89,0:52:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions died in World War I.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.26,0:52:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s Brother Franz’s statement
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.56,0:52:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that really gave\Nthe idea for the theme here:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.40,0:52:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“This Is It!”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.97,0:52:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The question arises, Will we have
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.04,0:52:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,one or more times\N—in the future or even now—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.81,0:52:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when we can say, “This is it”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.78,0:52:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and have that same exciting fervor
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.92,0:52:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because of Bible prophecy?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.82,0:52:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s begin with this one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.02,0:52:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Find Daniel chapter 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.43,0:52:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel chapter 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.10,0:52:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to read here verse 40,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.94,0:52:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or half of it:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.38,0:53:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the time of the end the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.81,0:53:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,(here at Daniel 11:40)\Nwill engage with him in a pushing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.72,0:53:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.62,0:53:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has been prayerfully considering recent events.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.29,0:53:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that in 1991,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.10,0:53:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet Union came to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.80,0:53:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So who is “the king of the north”?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.44,0:53:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, after prayerfully considering it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.44,0:53:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the matter of the pushing,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.74,0:53:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re assuring you that what we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.01,0:53:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,after prayerfully considering it,\Nis that it’s Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.95,0:53:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and its allies\N—the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.89,0:53:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s some reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.99,0:53:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Soviet Union disbanded;
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.29,0:53:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia came up from the rubble
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.93,0:53:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Soviet Union, along with its allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.67,0:54:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are some of the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.07,0:54:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Two things have become apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.74,0:54:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia and its allies\Nare continuing to engage
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.48,0:54:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in a pushing with the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.55,0:54:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll get to that “pushing” point shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.52,0:54:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second, they are taking the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.49,0:54:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in persecuting and opposing God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.12,0:54:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, notice what the pushing includes:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.76,0:54:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,electronic espionage,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.86,0:54:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,computer attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.23,0:54:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,trade wars
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.23,0:54:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(and that’s what they call them),
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.34,0:54:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hostile flooding\Ninto surrounding territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.41,0:54:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,These are recurring features\Nof the news headlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.68,0:54:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re aware of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.45,0:54:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So someone asks if the king\Nof the north has been inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.18,0:54:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.22,0:54:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears he’s never been this busy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.32,0:54:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with pushing the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.79,0:54:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.83,0:54:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, we’re confident\Nto share with you that Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.00,0:55:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and its allies are the king of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.93,0:55:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re engaged in this pushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.00,0:55:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, last month,\Nthey had the largest war games
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.70,0:55:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—Russia did—\Nsince the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.17,0:55:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was in existence way back in the ’80’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.21,0:55:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And they had their allies\Nwith them in the war game.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.78,0:55:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re confident this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.58,0:55:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the king of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.59,0:55:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s what’s involved at this time
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.32,0:55:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with the pushing—\Nlocking horns with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.43,0:55:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So is there going to be another time
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.26,0:55:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,related to Bible prophecy\Nwhere the faithful slave
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.97,0:55:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,will be able to say to you, “This is it”?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.67,0:55:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one that we’re all very familiar with
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.21,0:55:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—and especially\Nthis audience here in Newburgh,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.08,0:55:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ve been in the truth for decades—
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.81,0:55:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the very familiar thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.85,0:55:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from 1 Thessalonians chapter 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.25,0:55:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to read verse 2
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.52,0:56:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.46,0:56:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,5:2, 3:\N“For you yourselves know very well
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.00,0:56:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“that Jehovah’s day is coming exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.90,0:56:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“as a thief in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.37,0:56:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whenever it is that they are saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.34,0:56:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Peace and security!’
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.41,0:56:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“then sudden destruction\Nis to be instantly on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.44,0:56:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“just like birth pains on a pregnant woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.51,0:56:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will by no means escape.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.05,0:56:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, so that we have clear thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.62,0:56:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on the published comments regarding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.16,0:56:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,these two verses\Nthat we read, we’ll take you back
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.16,0:56:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to the September 15, 2012, Watchtower:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.37,0:56:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“As used here, ‘Jehovah’s day’
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.70,0:56:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“refers to the period\Nthat will start with the destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.41,0:56:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“of false religion and will culminate
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.64,0:56:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the war of Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.58,0:56:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“However, just before\Nthat day of Jehovah begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.08,0:57:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“world leaders will be saying,\N‘Peace and security!’
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.22,0:57:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“This may refer to one event
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.56,0:57:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“or to a series of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.39,0:57:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nations may think they are close
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.83,0:57:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to solving some of their big problems.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.43,0:57:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So here’s the question, and it’s understood
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.07,0:57:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that it would be asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.54,0:57:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the faithful slave\Nbe able to at a certain time
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.67,0:57:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,say to the brotherhood: “This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.38,0:57:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is what we’ve been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.41,0:57:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the ‘peace and security’ prophecy”?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.39,0:57:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep this comment in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.26,0:57:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from The Watchtower, 2004,\NFebruary 1, page 21:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.70,0:57:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Since Bible prophecies\Nare often fully understood
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.40,0:57:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“only after they are fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.94,0:57:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or are in the process of fulfillment . . .”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.24,0:57:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.04,0:57:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.61,0:58:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll come back to it,\Nand that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.11,0:58:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the case when\Nthe prophecy is fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.51,0:58:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh, OK.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.85,0:58:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But, see, we’ll come back
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.65,0:58:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to that statement\Nfrom The Watchtower shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.99,0:58:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But just consider\N(especially those of you here,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.16,0:58:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,many of you are aged,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.93,0:58:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.30,0:58:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,many of you who were\Nin the truth at the time),
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.43,0:58:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the year 1986?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.54,0:58:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The United Nations
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.74,0:58:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was proclaiming prior
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.41,0:58:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to January of 1986 that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.18,0:58:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, ‘Get ready.’
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.28,0:58:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They wanted\Nthe governments to put their arms down
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.25,0:58:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for at least a year,\Nthe International Year of Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.65,0:58:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.69,0:58:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you were in the truth back then,\Nyou were like, “OK.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.69,0:58:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So they were all big.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.73,0:58:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the pope at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.60,0:58:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gathered all these religious leaders
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.43,0:58:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,over there to Assisi, Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.70,0:59:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were all over there\Npraying to who they pray to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.51,0:59:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and having this fervor
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.44,0:59:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for peace for the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.88,0:59:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how did\Nthe faithful slave handle all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.68,0:59:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So this honors\NJehovah’s faithful slave serving at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.65,0:59:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what was published\Nin the ’85 Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.92,0:59:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,October 1, page 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.96,0:59:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is some months\Nbefore that all started in 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.60,0:59:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what was stated:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.00,0:59:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Christians cannot say in advance exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.94,0:59:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“when the great tribulation will strike.\N(Period.)
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.34,0:59:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah has not revealed\N‘that day or the hour.’
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.51,0:59:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thus when, for example, the United Nations
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.71,0:59:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares the year 1986
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.08,0:59:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“an ‘International Year of Peace,’
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.02,0:59:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Christians watch the event with interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.85,0:59:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“But they cannot say in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.52,0:59:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,whether this will prove\Nto be the fulfillment of Paul’s words.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.29,1:00:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, we kept on the watch,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.50,1:00:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but God’s spirit was guiding his people,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.30,1:00:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly the faithful slave.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.80,1:00:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They were not only faithful,\Nthey were discreet.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.04,1:00:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did not say:\N“This is it!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.24,1:00:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.24,1:00:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of 1 Thessalonians chapter 5.”\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.68,1:00:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you are still there,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,go back to 1 Thessalonians chapter 5
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.49,1:00:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—just something to keep in mind here—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.42,1:00:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes we’ll read\Nverses 2 and 3 and leave out verse 4.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.49,1:00:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He writes: “But you, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.86,1:00:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“you are not in darkness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.20,1:00:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the day should overtake\Nyou as it would thieves.”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.20,1:00:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So thieves are doing their thievery
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.01,1:00:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when it’s dark, but we’re sons of light.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.71,1:00:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s not going to catch us,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.41,1:00:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the faithful ones worshipping the true God,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.18,1:00:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,obedient to this\Nearthly part of his organization.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.69,1:00:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So the question comes up—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.99,1:01:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go back to that quote
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.36,1:01:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from the 2004 Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.09,1:01:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Prophecies are only fully understood\Nonly after they are fulfilled,’
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.33,1:01:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but we also said, ‘or are in the process
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.57,1:01:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of fulfillment.’
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.87,1:01:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So will
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.54,1:01:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the faithful slave be able to say
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.68,1:01:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the process of the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.78,1:01:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of this prophecy from 1 Thessalonians:\N“This is it!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.42,1:01:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we’ve been waiting for”?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.12,1:01:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll have to wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.03,1:01:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s a word of caution here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.76,1:01:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to pass on to you\Nbecause we’re all human.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.73,1:01:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We must keep on the watch,\Nbut please, just don’t be gullible.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.17,1:01:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear a world leader\Nsay something about peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.01,1:01:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you\Nstart e-mailing or something else
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.54,1:01:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with a social network.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.98,1:01:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is it!”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.48,1:02:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the channel to handle such matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.15,1:02:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If the faithful slave is moved by God’s spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.16,1:02:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that to the brotherhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.09,1:02:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s His will, fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.00,1:02:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But please don’t be gullible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.36,1:02:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Stick with the way\NJehovah wants this to operate,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.17,1:02:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’ll bless your obedience.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.94,1:02:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you’ll remember\NJehovah’s day begins
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.17,1:02:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as they’re saying,\N“Peace and security!”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.04,1:02:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn to Revelation chapter 17.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.91,1:02:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what stirring words!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.35,1:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They are familiar,\Nbut it does nourish our figurative hearts
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.76,1:02:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when we read these,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.13,1:02:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,chapter 17,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.93,1:02:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 15, 16, and 17:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.73,1:02:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to me: ‘The waters\Nthat you saw, where the prostitute
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.97,1:02:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘(the world empire of false religion) is sitting,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.64,1:02:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘mean peoples and crowds\Nand nations and tongues.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.57,1:03:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And the ten horns\Nthat you saw and the wild beast,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.48,1:03:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘these will hate the prostitute
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.81,1:03:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and will make her devastated and naked,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.48,1:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and they will eat up her flesh\Nand completely burn her with fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.55,1:03:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For God put it\Ninto their hearts to carry out his thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.16,1:03:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘yes, to carry out their one thought
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.39,1:03:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘by giving their kingdom to the wild beast,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.63,1:03:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,until the words of God\Nwill have been accomplished.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.43,1:03:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is what’s going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.20,1:03:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you think about it,\Nthis is just mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.61,1:03:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no plans as such
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.97,1:03:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—the governments—\Nat this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.71,1:03:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah forces
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.58,1:03:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one part of Satan’s system
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.15,1:03:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy another part.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.35,1:03:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the Almighty God can do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.89,1:03:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they do destroy Babylon the Great
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.16,1:03:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of this is taking place on the earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.70,1:03:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you brothers are not going\Nto need a breaking news update.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.17,1:04:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the globe you’re going to say:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.67,1:04:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is it!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.71,1:04:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The great tribulation has started.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.18,1:04:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.21,1:04:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who worry sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.75,1:04:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,during the great tribulation\Nas these events unfold,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.52,1:04:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re not going to be terrified.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.26,1:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re going to stand up straight,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.36,1:04:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lift your heads up, and say:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.27,1:04:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is it!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.70,1:04:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our deliverance is here.”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.85,1:05:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Brother Morris,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.32,1:05:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for heightening our eagerness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.35,1:05:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for what lies ahead in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.82,1:05:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you for removing the veil
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.49,1:05:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from “the king of the north.”
